notesStmt.note: Title from title page following table of contents (p. 1).
A preliminary title page appears before the table of contents: Estimation de Puigareau faite sous l'inspection du Sieur Chaillou, ingénieur géog[rap]he du Roi, 1769 (f. i recto).
Many pages marked with the stamp, "G. de Poitiers, Trois Sols."

msContents.summary: Complete dossier concerning the division of a large estate between Magdeleine-Angelique de Montmorency-Luxembourg and her older sister Anne-Françoise Charlotte de Montmorency-Luxembourg, including an abstract of proceedings and detailed inventories of the assets and values of three of the territories apportioned to Magdeleine-Angelique.

msItem.title: Procès-verbal d'estimation des terres et seigneuries, 1⁰ de Puigareau, 2⁰ de Luains, 3⁰ de la Cognoniere, apartenantes a Mademoiselle M. Magdeleine-Angelique de Montmorency-Luxembourg

supportDesc.extent: 288 leaves : 315 x 199 (251 x 140) mm. bound to 323 x 220 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, i (contemporary paper) + 288 + i (contemporary paper); [xviii], 1-247, 247-248, 248-261, 263-455, 446-538, [ix]; contemporary pagination in ink, upper outer corners.

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 25 long lines; ruled in lead.

binding.p: Contemporary calf with gilt spine and gilt Montmorency-Luxembourg arms on covers (front cover damaged).

history.provenance: Stamp on preliminary title page: Conseil d'état, 18 Avril 1823, No. 5627, Enregistrement.
Note in pencil inside front flyleaf suggests this volume was purchased by an earlier owner from Henri Saffroy, 1948.
